title: 820-3535 Finstack fault TH1H
message: No liquid ingress known. Fans run high. ASD shows TH1H below limit but when I check FINSTACKSNS_ALERT_L, it always reads 3.3V with or without the IO cable connected. I've tried 3 different IO cables and IO boards. DIode reading at pin 21 J9500 = .53. Replaced the SMC twice and checked for continuity from R5172 to corresponding pad 123 under SMC. I get 3v3 at TP SMC SENSOR ALERT. I'm at a loss as to what is causing this fault.

title: 820-3535 Finstack fault TH1H
message: Tried those and was hopeful but: Still getting fault.

title: 820-3535 Finstack fault TH1H
message:
A signal like ALERT_L is good to have it high; problem appears if low.
Mentioned signal is active low, remember.

Is that the only error which appers on ASD?

title: 820-3535 Finstack fault TH1H
message: right. Thats why I thought it was SMC. Could this be PCH issue? Yes that is the only error. I've run ASD probably 5 times and Finstack TH1H is only error.

title: 820-3535 Finstack fault TH1H
message:
Did you set continue, instead of stop on first error?

Good trackpad must be connected, as LIO board too.
If not, fan spins to max and error comes up too.

Did you try disconnecting webcam?

title: 820-3535 Finstack fault TH1H
message: Correct, ASD set to continue so only the one actual error. Disconnecting webcam didn't change anything

title: 820-3535 Finstack fault TH1H
message:
Check Q/C5830 and traces to U5800.
Also check R5370/71 and their traces to J9500.

title: 820-3535 Finstack fault TH1H
message: SOLVEd. Thanks for your help. Had a very high diode reading on pin 1 of R5370 so it was not getting PP3V3_S3. Jumpered that and all is well!
